@Nora 

It's easy for you to say (probably) - in the past two weeks alone at least two of my typical comments, each 1500 characters long, never appeared on the board, and I have no idea why. Probably more than a dozen short comments of mine were lost in the nether in the same period, on top of that.

I wrote an email about it to the NYT games section a week ago but I didn't even get a reply, not even a generic "Thank you for your message, now go away". So when my post does not show up after I refresh the page several times, I assume it may have been rejected, and I am not prepared to accept that. When a major newspaper runs a comment board, it should work in predictable ways. It's not me who is in the wrong here, it's the NYT, and I will not keep quiet about it.

